    "description": {
      "en": {
        "provenance": "imported",
        "value": "Contribute to reduce public sector corruption in Nepal, by strenghtening the anti-corruption movement and public integrity in key service institutions, sectors and society. The project will focus its interventions in nine districts of Nepal namely Siraha, Dolakha, Rautahat, Bhaktapur, Rupandehi, Baglung, Banke, Dang and Darchula and at central level in Kathmandu. Reaching directly more than 15 000 people from: i) Government of Nepal, ii) key public service-delivery organizations especially education, energy and local development, iii) victims and witness of corruption, iv)  affiliated partner organizations, v) general public, vi) politicians and vii) media"
      },
